<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="416" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1231,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Greek word 
<emphasis box="[819,896,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">perone</emphasis>
, a pointed item aimed at piercing. This refers to the acute apex of the phallus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
